description.narrative: 3.3 Families and communities are more aware of the needs of young children and mothers on health, nutrition, Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) and development, and are more engaged in demanding for Early Childhood Development and Early Childhood Intervention services for children with disabilities, which contributes to Children With Disabilities, Early Childhood Development, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more vulnerable children and mothers have access to quality comprehensive health and nutritional systems and better able to survive and reach their optimal development.

description.narrative: UNICEF and MoSD as lead of the social sector, introduced the innovative real-time monitoring platform (RapidPro) to serve as a channel of communication for families with children with disabilities and the respective service providers. In addition, community mobilization services to increase the awareness of families and communities on the needs of young children and mothers on health, nutrition, WASH and development were achieved resulting in the enhancement of care givers knowledge and practices toward addressing the needs of their children.
